did.unittitle: Yale Cabaret Scripts and Ephemera Collection
did.abstract: This collection contains scripts and ephemera from the Yale Cabaret.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: The Yale Cabaret Scripts and Ephemera Collection was housed in the former Drama Library until its transfer to the Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library in 2008.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Copyright has not been transferred to Yale University.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Yale Cabaret Scripts and Ephemera Collection, Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library, Yale University.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection contains scripts produced by and ephemera pertaining to the Yale Cabaret.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The Yale Cabaret is a theater managed and produced by Yale School of Drama students. The Cabaret stages about 20 productions per year. It provides a unique performance setting which includes under 100 reconfigurable seats. The theater produces two performances per evening, serving food and beverage. These productions include adaptations of published plays, student-written plays, and collaboratively devised pieces.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Organized into two series: I. Scripts. II. Ephemera.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Arranged chronologically by year of production, then alphabetically by author's last name.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series includes ephemera such as posters, programs, photographs, clippings, advertisements, and newsletters pertaining to the Yale Cabaret.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Arranged chronologically by year and then by month and day of performance.
